#: ../../N/nastygram.rst:5
msgid "nastygram"
msgstr "nastygram"

#: ../../N/nastygram.rst:7
msgid "/nas´tee·gram/, n\\."
msgstr "/nas´tee·gram/, 名詞"

#: ../../N/nastygram.rst:10
msgid ""
"A protocol packet or item of email (the latter is also called a "
":ref:`letterbomb`\\) that takes advantage of misfeatures or security holes "
"on the target system to do untoward things."
msgstr ""
"標的システムの欠陥やセキュリティホールを利用して、よからぬことをするプロトコルパケットまたは電子メール(後者は\\ "
":ref:`letterbomb`\\ とも呼ばれる)。"

#: ../../N/nastygram.rst:13
msgid ""
"Disapproving mail, esp. from a :ref:`net-god`\\, pursuant to a violation of "
":ref:`netiquette` or a complaint about failure to correct some mail- or "
"news-transmission problem. Compare :ref:`shitogram`\\, :ref:`mailbomb`\\."
msgstr ""
"不賛成のメール。特に\\ :ref:`net-god`\\ から、\\ :ref:`netiquette`\\ "
"違反に伴って、あるいはメールやニュース伝送の問題を修正しなかったことへの苦情として送られるもの。\\ :ref:`shitogram`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`mailbomb`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../N/nastygram.rst:18
msgid ""
"A status report from an unhappy, and probably picky, customer. \"What'd "
"Corporate say in today's nastygram?\""
msgstr "不満を抱えた、おそらくうるさい顧客からの状況報告。「今日のnastygramでCorporateは何て言ってきた?」"

#: ../../N/nastygram.rst:22
msgid ""
"[deprecated] An error reply by mail from a :ref:`daemon`\\; in particular, a"
" :ref:`bounce-message`\\."
msgstr "[非推奨] \\ :ref:`daemon`\\ からのメールによるエラー返答。特に\\ :ref:`bounce-message`\\ 。"
